Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Full-stack Software Engineer* role with *Adobe Workfront*. I bring over three years of software engineering experience across AI-powered platforms and full-stack product development, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I owned end-to-end build, development, testing, fixing, optimization, and continuous improvement of an MCP AI interaction layer built with Node.js, TypeScript/ES6, and Python across 1000+ platform endpoints. I partnered with Product Management and UX to deliver customer-focused features from architecture through iteration, and I designed orchestration for distributed or cloud-based systems (AWS, GCP, Azure) using high-availability concepts that remained reliable under significant load. I also optimized concurrency and routing to reduce latency by 60% and lower API cost by 50%, directly aligning with Adobe's emphasis on high-impact, scalable engineering execution.

Earlier at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Java, Spring Boot, and AWS that supported thousands of users across 30+ applications while meeting WCAG 2.1 AA standards. I also developed Step Functions-based backend workflows and collaborated on service boundaries spanning RDBMS, NoSQL, Kafka, Elasticsearch, Docker, and Kubernetes. Combined with my research work at Pace AI Lab and workshops for 50+ students, this experience has strengthened both technical communication and cross-functional collaboration.

Adobe's mission to empower everyone, everywhere to imagine, create, and bring any digital experience to life strongly resonates with me. I am especially energized by your focus on *unleashing creativity* and *accelerating productivity*, and I would value the opportunity to contribute to Adobe's goal through customer-focused platform engineering.

I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, and I look forward to connecting.

